                          Node- Server/back end technology


                                   basic commands


                            1.create package.json - npm init

                            2.install express - npm i express

                            3.install nodemon - npm i -g nodemon

                            4. install jwt token-npm i jsonwebtoken

                            5.to compile - nodemon index.js

                            6. install mongoose - npm i mongoose

                            7.install cors-npm i cors







                                   basic steps

                            1. create package.json

                            2.install express

                            3.create index.js file

                            4.import express

                            5.create Server app using express

                            6.set a port number for Server

                            7.client HTTP request resolving
                               syntax : Server-app.HTTP-request(path,callback)

                            8. response status code
                               1xx-information
                               2xx-success
                               3xx-redirection
                               4xx-client side error
                               5xx-Server side error



                            9.import jsonwebtoken

                               9.1 jwt token-user validation
                               
                                 9.1.1 token generation -sign()
                                 9.1.2 token verify-verify()



                           10.middleware - 
                               10.1 application specific
                               10.2 router specific

                           11.mongo db connection
                             11.1 install mongoose
                             11.2 create db.js file
                             11.3.import mongoose in db.js
                             11.4.state connection string using mongoose
                             11,5.create model/collection
                             11.6.export model

                           12. asynchronous function resolving- promise
                               12.1 resolved state- .then()
                               12.2 reject state- catch()---error

                           13.CORS-cross origin resource sharing